{{Infobox company | name = Modernizing Medicine | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. "fr" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. --> | former_name = | type = Privately held company | industry = Software | founded = February 2010 | founder = Daniel Cane, Dr. Michael Sherling | hq_location = | hq_location_city = Boca Raton | hq_location_country = United States | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = EMA electronic health records system, Practice Management, Analytics, Kiosk, Telehealth, Pathology module, Inventory Management; gGastro EHR, gPM, Endoscopy Report Writer | brands = | services = Revenue Cycle Management, MIPS Advisory Services | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | ratio = <!-- for BANKS ONLY --> | rating = <!-- for BANKS ONLY --> | website = https://www.modmed.com/ }}
'''Modernizing Medicine, Inc.''', is a [[software]] [[software company|company]] headquartered at the Research Park at [[Florida Atlantic University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Research Park at Florida Atlantic University|url=http://www.research-park.org/research-park-companies|accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref> in [[Boca Raton, Florida|Boca Raton]], [[Florida]]. The company has two co-founders: [[Daniel Cane]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Pounds|first=Marcia|title=Excalibur Award: Daniel Cane, Modernizing Medicine|url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/palm-beach/fl-daniel-cane-20140413,0,3897738,full.story|publisher=Sun Sentinel|accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref> CEO and co-founder of Blackboard, Inc.,<ref>{{cite web|title=Blackboard History – History of Blackboard|url=http://www.gilfuseducationgroup.com/blackboard-history-e-true-hollywood-story|publisher=Gilfus Education Group|accessdate=21 April 2014}}</ref> and Dr. Michael Sherling,<ref>{{cite web|title=Palm Beach Dermatology|url=http://www.palmbeachskin.com/Physicians--Locations/Michael-Sherling-MD|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref> Chief Medical and Strategy Officer and practicing dermatologist.
The company offers electronic health records, practice management, revenue cycle management and data analytics for doctors, and currently has software for [[Dermatology|dermatologists]], [[Ophthalmology|ophthalmologists]], orthopedic surgeons, gastroenterologists, plastic surgeons, ENTs (or otolaryngologists), urologists and pain management physicians. As part of its business model, Modernizing Medicine employs practicing doctors to help program the software for each specialty.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fisher|first=Anne|title=Could teaching employees to code be key to success?|url=http://money.cnn.com/2013/10/25/smallbusiness/modernizing-medicine-code/index.html|publisher=CNN Money|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Byrne|first=Ciara|title=Why Doctors Make Great Object-Oriented Software Designers|url=http://www.fastcolabs.com/3022965/open-company/why-doctors-make-great-object-oriented-software-designers|publisher=Fast Company|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Rogers|first=Bruce|title=Will Daniel Cane's Modernizing Medicine Revolutionize Healthcare?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/brucerogers/2013/12/19/will-daniel-canes-modernizing-medicine-revolutionize-healthcare/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref>
The company has raised $332 million in funding, most recently with $231 million from private equity group Warburg Pincus in 2017. Modernizing Medicine acquired gMed, a healthcare IT company serving gastroenterologists, in 2015. In October 2016, Modernizing Medicine hired its 500th employee. In addition to its Boca Raton, Florida, headquarters, the company also has offices in Roseville, California and Santiago, Chile.
