'''Paul Anthony Lee''' {{Post-nominals|country=GBR|DL}} (born January 1946) is a British lawyer and businessperson who since 2009 has been the Chairman of the [[Horserace Betting Levy Board]].

== Career ==
Lee read Law at [[Clare College, Cambridge]] and joined Addleshaw Sons & Latham, specialising in corporate finance. He became a Managing Partner at the firm in 1991, then Senior Partner in the post-merger [[Addleshaw Booth & Co]] in 1997, and finally  a Senior Partner in [[Addleshaw Goddard]] in 2001, until he retired in May 2010.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.addleshawgoddard.com/view.asp?content_id=4688&parent_id=968|title=Paul Lee appointed as new Chair of the Horserace Betting Levy Board  - Addleshaw Goddard|website=www.addleshawgoddard.com|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/paul-lee-reappointed-as-chairman-of-horserace-betting-levy-board|title=Paul Lee reappointed as Chairman of Horserace Betting Levy Board - Publications - GOV.UK|website=www.gov.uk|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref>

Lee is a board member of the [[Confederation of British Industry]], and was the Chairman of CBI North West. He has also served as Trustee and later Chairman of the [[Royal Exchange, Manchester|Royal Exchange Theatre]] in Manchester (1991–2016), as the Chairman of the [[Feoffee|Feoffees]] of [[Chetham's School of Music]], and on the boards of the [[Hallé Concerts Society]], [[Opera North]], the [[Northern Ballet]], the [[University of Manchester]], and other cultural institutions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.manchester.ac.uk/discover/governance/structure/board-governors/members/paul-lee/|title=Paul Lee {{!}} Board of Governors {{!}} The University of Manchester|website=www.manchester.ac.uk|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref>

Lee was appointed as Chairman of the Horserace Betting Levy Board by the [[Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport]] starting from 1 October 2009, succeeding [[Robert Valentine Hughes]].<ref name=":0" /> He was re-appointed for another four-year term starting in 2013.<ref name=":1" />

Lee, a [[Deputy Lieutenant]] for [[Greater Manchester]], served as the [[High Sheriff of Greater Manchester]] for 2014–15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/notice/L-60799-2010570|title=Duchy of Lancaster|website=www.thegazette.co.uk|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://manchesterlieutenancy.org/Lee_Paul|title=Greater Manchester Lieutenancy - Paul A Lee Esq DL MA LLB|website=manchesterlieutenancy.org|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref>

